1- Frameworks
    a- Flutter
    b- React Native
2- UI libraries
    a- Material Design (Flutter)
    b- React Native Paper
3- State management
    a- Flutter: provier or riverpod
    b- React Native: Redux or Zustand


Backend
1- Frameworks
    a- Spring Framework
    b- Node.js
    c- Django
2- Authentication
    a- Firebase Authentication (if using firebase)
    b- JSON Web Tokens (JWT) for custom authentication
        Spring Security with JWT
3- Rest Api or GraphQL
    a- GraphQL: flexible querying for advanced features


Database
1- Relational
    a- PostgreSQL
    b- SQLite
    c- H2 in memory Database for development

3- ORM
    a- Spring Data JPA with Hibernate for database interactions

2- NoSQL
    a- Firebase Firestore
    b- MongoDb

Other Tools:
1- Version control
    a- *Github or Gitlab
2- CI/CD
    a- Github Actions or CircleCI
3- Testing
    a- Unit Testing: Jest (React Native) or Flutter Test
    b- End to End Testing: Cypress or Appium

4- API Documentation
    a- Swagger or OpenAI for documenting and testing APIs

5- Build Tool
    a- Maven or Gradle

6- Hosting
    a- Google cloud
    b- AWS
    c- Azure
    d- Heroku for simlicity